  "id": "019d32e2-4351-7461-b84a-3b0ab045eb8b",
  "content": "# PostgresStore tsvector (Phase 2b) -- Design Decisions (2026-03-28)\n\n## What: Implement FullTextSearchable for PostgresStore using native PostgreSQL tsvector.\n\n## Key Decisions:\n1. tsvector column is NOT a GENERATED ALWAYS AS column. PostgreSQL does not allow GENERATED columns to reference other generated columns or be used with ALTER TABLE ADD COLUMN ... GENERATED in all cases reliably. Instead, we use a trigger-maintained tsvector column populated on INSERT/UPDATE, plus a GIN index for fast lookup.\n2. search_text() uses ts_rank_cd (cover density ranking) with plainto_tsquery for safe query parsing. Scores are raw positive values (not normalized); BM25Searcher handles normalization.\n3. index_entry/remove_entry/flush are no-ops for PostgresStore because tsvector is auto-maintained by the trigger and SQL is transactional.\n4. rebuild_from_store() regenerates all tsvector values via UPDATE SET content = content (triggers re-fire).\n5. The FullTextSearchable trait currently only defines search_text(). The additional methods from the design doc (D5) are not yet in the trait, so this implementation only adds search_text().\n\n## Alternatives rejected:\n- pg_bm25 extension: adds external dependency, not available in standard pgvector image\n- Manual tsvector population in application code: more error-prone than trigger/generated column approach",
